## §R8 Data Exposure Requirements

### R8.1 What Can Be Exposed via api_public

**✅ ALLOWED (via api_public views/RPC):**
- `video_segments_feed` - Curated, public-facing segments
- `my_account_state` - User's own tier/quota info
- `user_favorites` - User's own saved segments (filtered by auth.uid())
- Aggregated statistics (total segments, popular keywords)

**❌ FORBIDDEN (never expose directly):**
- `youtube_videos_staging` - Internal staging table
- `youtube_videos_operational` - Internal operational table
- Internal IDs (staging.id, operational.id)
- Processing status fields (pending, processing, failed)
- API keys, service credentials
- Other users' data (must filter by auth.uid())

### R8.2 Exposure Pattern

**Use views with SECURITY INVOKER:**
```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW api_public.video_segments_feed
WITH (security_invoker = true)
AS
SELECT
  segment_hash,      -- ✅ External identifier
  title,
  description,
  published_at,
  keyword,
  thumbnail_url,
  video_duration
  -- ❌ NO: id, operational_video_id, staging_id, processing_status
FROM public.video_segments_operational
WHERE status = 'published'
  AND (tier_requirement <= get_user_tier_id() OR get_user_tier_id() >= 20); -- Tier filtering
```

**Use RPC for writes with SECURITY DEFINER:**
```sql
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION api_public.save_favorite_segment(
  p_segment_hash text
)
RETURNS uuid
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
SET search_path TO 'public', 'pg_temp'
AS $$
BEGIN
  INSERT INTO public.user_favorites (user_id, segment_hash)
  VALUES (auth.uid(), p_segment_hash)
  RETURNING id;
END;
$$;
```

### R8.3 Verification Checklist

Before exposing any data via `api_public`:
- [ ] Uses external identifiers (segment_hash), not internal IDs
- [ ] Filters by `auth.uid()` for user-specific data
- [ ] Applies tier-based access controls
- [ ] Uses SECURITY INVOKER for reads (RLS applies)
- [ ] Uses SECURITY DEFINER + `SET search_path` for writes
- [ ] No internal status fields exposed
- [ ] No sensitive metadata exposed
- [ ] Grants are explicit (REVOKE ALL, then GRANT specific roles)

