## §R9 Update Guidelines

### When to Update This File

**Update requirements.mdc when:**
- Adding new features (new functional requirements)
- Changing business logic (tier quotas, filtering rules)
- Modifying data flow (fetch → transform → distribute)
- Updating AI prompts (segment extraction logic)
- Adding/removing trusted channels
- Changing negative filters

**DO NOT update when:**
- Fixing bugs (that's implementation, not requirements)
- Refactoring code (no functional change)
- Optimizing performance (implementation detail)
- Changing database indexes (implementation detail)

### Requirements vs Implementation

**Requirements (this file):**
- WHAT the system must do
- Business rules
- User-facing features
- Data validation rules

**Implementation (core-rules.mdc, pipeline-rules.mdc):**
- HOW to implement
- Technical patterns
- Code examples
- Error handling

**Example:**
- ✅ Requirement: "MUST filter gambling keywords" (§R3.1)
- ✅ Implementation: "Use negativeFilters.ts with regex patterns" (pipeline-rules.mdc)

