## §R10 SEO & Discovery Requirements

### R10.1 Sitemap

**MUST:**
- Expose a dynamic `sitemap.xml` for search engine crawlers.
- Generate sitemap via Edge Function (not static file) so it includes all indexable URLs (news, chronicles, static pages).
- Limit sitemap generation to max 1000 URLs per content type (news, chronicles, video klipp `/klipp/:segmentHash`) to protect database load.
- Cache sitemap response for at least 1 hour (`Cache-Control: public, max-age=3600`).
- Include homepage, `/om-oss`, and all public article/chronicle URLs with `lastmod` and `priority`. Do **not** list `/auth` or other non-indexable pages in the sitemap.

**MUST NOT:**
- Expose internal or admin URLs in the sitemap.
- Omit the sitemap URL from `robots.txt` (Sitemap directive must point to production URL).

**Implementation:** Edge Function `sitemap`; Vercel rewrite `/sitemap.xml` → Supabase Edge Function. See core-rules.mdc §0.9 (Vercel rewrites), §7 (anti-scraping limits).

### R10.2 About Page (E-E-A-T)

**MUST:**
- Provide a dedicated "Om oss" (About) page at `/om-oss`.
- Content MUST state that the site is "by supporters, for supporters" and is not an official AIK product.
- Include mission, how content is aggregated (e.g. AI curation), and a contact method (e.g. email).
- Use unique `<title>` and `<meta name="description">` for the About page (SEO component).

**MUST NOT:**
- Claim official affiliation with AIK Fotboll or AIK Hockey unless true.

**Implementation:** `src/pages/About.tsx`; route `/om-oss`; footer link in Layout.

### R10.3 Social Previews (Open Graph / Twitter)

**MUST:**
- Serve correct Open Graph and Twitter Card meta tags for shared links (chronicles, news).
- Use a server-side proxy (Edge Function) for bot user-agents so crawlers receive full HTML with meta tags; humans are redirected to the SPA.
- Bot detection MUST include: facebookexternalhit, facebot, twitterbot, linkedinbot, whatsapp, telegrambot, slackbot, googlebot, bingbot, yandex, baiduspider.
- Canonical share URL format: `https://aikurerad.se/share/{type}/{id}` (type = chronicle | news).

**MUST NOT:**
- Expose open-redirect via share URLs; origin allowlist (aikurerad.se, localhost, vercel preview) is required.

**Implementation:** Edge Function `share-proxy`; Vercel rewrites `/share/chronicle/:slug` and `/share/news/:id` to share-proxy. See core-rules.mdc §0.9.

### R10.4 Legacy URL Handling

**MUST:**
- Support legacy query-param deep links: `/?chronicle=<slug>` and `/?news=<id>` by redirecting (client-side) to `/chronicle/<slug>` and `/news/<id>`.

**Implementation:** `src/pages/Index.tsx` (useEffect reading searchParams and calling navigate).

